  <fr:p>Let <fr:tex>\chi _x \colon  a = x</fr:tex> be the witness of contraction for any <fr:tex>x:A</fr:tex>. Given <fr:tex>b : Ba</fr:tex> and <fr:tex>x:A</fr:tex>, we define <fr:tex>\mathsf {ind}_{A,a}\,b\,x : Bx</fr:tex> by transporting <fr:tex>b</fr:tex> along the identification <fr:tex>\chi _a^{-1} \cdot  \chi _x \colon  a = x</fr:tex>:</fr:p>

  <fr:tex
display="block">     \mathsf {ind}_{A,a}\,b\,x :\equiv      \mathopen {}\left ({\chi _a^{-1}\cdot \chi _x}\right )\mathclose {}_* b   </fr:tex>

  <fr:p>Then we compute <fr:tex>\mathsf {ind}_{A,a}\,b\,a \equiv  \mathopen {}\left ({\chi _a^{-1}\cdot \chi _a}\right )\mathclose {}_* b  = \mathsf {refl}_*b = b</fr:tex>.</fr:p>
